main event: A school supply helper reported seeing a rapidly rotating, circular object at an altitude of approximately 35,000 feet over Portland, Oregon.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 2-3 minutes before disappearing in the distance traveling in a southerly direction.
The object's flight path and maneuvers were similar to those of a military aircraft, but the case could not be definitively explained.
No physical evidence was found, and the final evaluation was that there was insufficient information to provide any definite conclusions.
A check of air traffic in the area indicated that the object could have been a C-47 or C-54 aircraft, but this was not confirmed.
The report mentions a temperature inversion at 9,000 feet with a possible haze layer, which could have caused the object to appear unusual.
